-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2016/10/26 (Git instruction updated)   
2016/10/20 (Git instruction original)   
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Setup local repository (For users who do not need to upload his/her codes.)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ cd <your_working_directory>
$ git init
$ git clone git://github.com/ILC-TPC-Asia/yokaRawMonNeo.git
$ cd yokaRawMonNeo
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) Setup local repository (For developers)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ cd <your_working_directory>
$ git init
$ git clone https://github.com/ILC-TPC-Asia/yokaRawMonNeo.git
$ cd yokaRawMonNeo
$ git checkout -b dev

To upload source codes (In yokaRawMonNeo directory):
$ git add <modified_file_names>
$ git commit -m "WRITE COMMENTS HERE."
$ git push origin dev:master 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------


0) Preparation of KalTest
$ cd KalTest
$ source ./setup
$ make

1) Building yokaRowMonNeo
$ cd ../yokaRawMonNeo
$ source ./setup.sh
$ make

2) How to Run
$ cd unpacker
$ ./unpacker.sh <rawdata_file>
$ cd trackmaker
$ run -l reco.C

3) How to do many runs at one time
$ vi manyrun.sh
.....
layer=21              # select layer to look at
inout=\"in\"          # include the layer in fitting
#inout=\"out\"        # exculde the layer from fitting
......
$ ./manyrun.sh
